com.lge.qcircle.template

Class TemplateTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lge.qcircle.template.TemplateTag

  • public final class TemplateTag
extends java.lang.Object
    This class provides IDs of content views which are on the circle.

    You can get the layout of a content view by using QCircleTemplate.getLayoutById(int) with a constant of this class.

    See Also:
    QCircleTemplate.getLayoutById(int)

    • Field Detail

      • CONTENT

        public static final int CONTENT
        top content.

        If it has any children, you can set them, too.

      • CONTENT_MAIN

        public static final int CONTENT_MAIN
        main content.

        If you use an empty template, it is identical to CONTENT. If you use an template which has any side bars, it means a child view of the top content excluding sidebars.

      • CONTENT_SIDE_1

        public static final int CONTENT_SIDE_1
        the first sidebar.

        If you use an empty template, it cannot be used. If you use an template which has any side bars, it means the first sidebar.

      • CONTENT_SIDE_2

        public static final int CONTENT_SIDE_2
        the second sidebar.

        If you use an empty template or an template with one sidebar, it cannot be used. If you use an template which has two side bars, it means the second sidebar.
